{{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = Art in the San Francisco Bay Area, 1945-1980 | image = Art in the San Francisco Bay Area Thomas Albright.jpg | caption = | author = [[Thomas Albright]] | title_orig = | translator = | illustrator = Various | cover_artist = | country = | language = | series = | subject = Art history, the [[San Francisco Bay Area]] | genre = | publisher = University of California Press | pub_date = 1985 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Hardcover | pages = | isbn = 0-520-051939 | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''Art in the San Francisco Bay Area, 1945-1980: An Illustrated History''''' is a 1985 nonfiction book by art critic [[Thomas Albright]], about the modern history of art in the [[San Francisco Bay Area]]. It was published by the [[University of California Press]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Art in the San Francisco Bay Area, 1945-1980 AN IllUSTRATED HISTORY : by Thomas Albright (University of California: $60, hardback; $35, paperback; 360 pp.; 115 color and 118 black-and-white reproductions)|date=August 11, 1985|first=William|last=Wilson|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1985-08-11/books/bk-2632_1_san-francisco-art|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]}}</ref>
==Subjects== Albright covers the movements in modern art in which the Bay Area were heavily involved, and their practitioners, including [[Clyfford Still]] and [[Abstract Expressionism]], the [[Modernist]] school, [[Pop Art]], [[Formalism (art)|Formalism]], The [[Bay Area Figurative Movement]], [[Conceptual art]], [[Photorealism]], and others.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.clintreilly.com/thomas-albright/ |title=Thomas Albright |last=Reilly |first=Clint |date=August 27, 2007 |website=Clintreilly.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100305004042/http://www.clintreilly.com/thomas-albright/ |archivedate=March 5, 2010 |deadurl=yes}}</ref> The book contains numerous reproductions of the works discussed.
