{{Infobox library | image = | library_name = Bergen County Cooperative Library System | library_logo = [[File:Bergen County Cooperative Library System logo.jpg|300 px]] | location = Northern New Jersey | established = 1979 | num_branches = 77 | collection_size = 5,000,000<ref name="Values">{{cite web|title=FAQ|url=http://bccls.org/help/faq.shtml|accessdate=20 February 2017}}</ref> | annual_circulation = 11.2 million (2013)<ref name="Numbers" /> | pop_served = 1.2 million<ref name="Numbers" /> | members = 670,000<ref name="Numbers">{{cite web|title=What Is "Buckles"?|url=http://www.bccls.org/about_BCCLS/what_is_bccls.shtml|accessdate=20 February 2017}}</ref> | budget = | director = | website = http://bccls.org }} The '''Bergen County Cooperative Library System''' ('''BCCLS''') is a consortium of [[public library|public libraries]] in the four northeastern [[New Jersey]] [[Gateway Region]] counties of [[Bergen County, New Jersey|Bergen]], [[Hudson County, New Jersey|Hudson]], [[Passaic County, New Jersey|Passaic]], and [[Essex County, New Jersey|Essex]]. Founded in 1979, the organization allows for reciprocal borrowing among its members so that books, audiobooks, CDs, DVDs and other media are shared among the libraries cooperatively.<ref>[http://www.newmilfordboro.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=71&Itemid=97 ]{{dead link|date=July 2018}}</ref> Those with a valid library card from participating towns are permitted to reserve materials online and have them transferred to their local library, where materials can be retrieved.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bccls.org/|title=BCCLS|website=www.bccls.org}}</ref>
In 2015, there were 77 public libraries with a total of 81 branches participating in the consortium.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.librarytechnology.org/libraries.pl?Consortia=Bergen+County+Cooperative+Library+System|title=libraries.org: search results -- the library is a member of Bergen County Cooperative Library System|website=www.librarytechnology.org}}</ref> All of Bergen County’s public libraries are members of the Bergen County Cooperative Library System along with 15 libraries from Essex, Hudson, and Passaic. A patron’s hometown library card is honored at all participating libraries. The BCCLS had also participated in the Open Borrowing (www.openborrowing.org) program, with participating libraries in Middlesex, Morris, Passaic, Sussex and Warren counties; this participation ended on January 1, 2015.<ref>[http://www.passaicpubliclibrary.org/flyers/2014_12_04_Open_Borrow.pdf ]{{dead link|date=July 2018}}</ref>
