{{unreferenced|date=March 2012}} [[File:Vide-poche.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Coin tray in [[Pottery|ceramics]] in ''[[Raku ware|raku]]''-style).]]
A '''coin tray''' is a container, used to receive various small items such as [[coins]], [[key (lock)|keys]] or [[train ticket|transport tickets]] from trouser pockets. For example, when getting undressed before going to bed.
There are coin trays in [[ceramic]], [[leather]], [[metal]], [[textile]] or [[wood]]. The edges may be more or less flat.
[[File:Ellie holding the coin tray.jpg|thumb|left|Numimatist with a coin tray]]
== Coin-tray for [[numismatics]] use == Some coin trays are specialized for protecting and showing collections of coins.
{{Clear}}
