'''''enRoute''''' is the [[in-flight magazine]] and entertainment system of [[Air Canada]]. All content in the monthly magazine is published in both [[French (language)|French]] and [[English (language)|English]] by [[Spafax]]. The magazine is headquartered in [[Montreal, Quebec]].<ref name="cnw">{{cite news|title=Air Canada's enRoute wins 10 National Magazine Awards|url=http://www.newswire.ca/news-releases/air-canadas-enroute-wins-10-national-magazine-awards-537831331.html|accessdate=5 June 2016|work=CNW|location=Montreal}}</ref>
==History and profile== The magazine is offered for free on all Air Canada aircraft and in its [[Maple Leaf Lounge]]s. The publisher of the magazine is Spafax Canada Inc.<ref>{{cite news|title=About enRoute|url=http://www.spafax.com/press/air-canadas-enroute-magazine-in-partnership-with-interior-designers-of-canada-and-iidexneocon-canada-announces-the-winners-of-the-first-ever-enroute-hotel-design-awards/|accessdate=3 April 2016|work=Spafax Canada Inc}}</ref>
As well as the magazine, ''enRoute'' is the name given to Air Canada's in-flight entertainment programme of movies, television, radio and short films, available on most flights.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.spafax.com/case-studies/air-canada/publishing-case-study-enroute-magazinebrandmedia |title=Case Study: enRoute magazine/brand/media |work=[[Spafax]] |date=2011 |accessdate=14 November 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130621160904/http://www.spafax.com/case-studies/air-canada/publishing-case-study-enroute-magazinebrandmedia |archivedate=21 June 2013 |df= }}</ref>
Ilana Weitzman served as the [[editor-in-chief]] of the magazine until July 2015 when she was replaced by Jean-François Légaré.<ref>{{cite news|title=enRoute has a new editor-in-chief|url=http://www.mastheadonline.com/news/enroute_has_a_new_editorinchief/|accessdate=5 June 2016|work=Masthead|date=27 July 2015|location=Toronto}}</ref> Stefanie Sosiak serves as Art Director (as of October 2015).
==Reception== In 2009 ''enRoute'' won 10 awards at the [[Canadian National Magazine Awards]].<ref name="cnw"/> In May 2012 [[cnn.com]] named it as the best inflight magazine worldwide.<ref>{{cite news|author=Denis Krik|title=Ranking der besten Inflight-Magazine: Abgehobene Lektüre|url=http://www.spiegel.de/reise/fernweh/ranking-der-inflight-magazine-lufthansa-magazin-unter-den-besten-a-832478.html|accessdate=5 June 2016|work=Der Spiegel|date=10 May 2012|language=German}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=enRoute named world's best inflight magazine by CNN |url=http://www.the-cma.com/news/enroute-named-worlds-best-inflight-magazine-by-cnn |accessdate=5 June 2016 |work=Content Marketing Association }}{{dead link|date=December 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
==Air Canada enRoute Film Festival== The magazine previously ran the [[Air Canada enRoute Film Festival]]. The festival ran from 2007<ref>[http://enroute.aircanada.com/en/articles/enroute-student-film-festival-2007 Enroute student film festival 2007]</ref> until 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.spafax.com/case-studies/air-canada/air-canadas-enroute-student-film-festival# |title=Enroute student film festival |access-date=2012-11-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130708165622/http://www.spafax.com/case-studies/air-canada/air-canadas-enroute-student-film-festival# |archive-date=2013-07-08 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> The festival had a different jury each year consisting of [[film industry]] professionals including famous actors, writers, directors and producers. The festival's purpose was to generate exposure for emerging filmmakers.
