'''Frame conservation''' is the preservation of [[picture frame]]s. This involves replicating missing decorative elements, cleaning, gilding, and toning frame surfaces.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.americanart.si.edu/lunder/studio.cfm?key=2 |title=What happens in the frames studio? |publisher=Lunder Conservation Center |accessdate=July 19, 2013}}</ref>
==Gilding== [[File:Gilded frame being burnished with agate tool.jpg|thumb|250px|Picture of a gilded frame ready to be burnished with an agate tool]] {{Main|Gilding}} Gilding, in the context of frame preservation, describes the process by which metal leaf is applied to a frame to restore areas of the preexisting leaf that have damage.
==Toning== {{Main|Tints and shades}}
